    <introduction>
      <p>
        Companies such as Pew Research frequently conduct polls as a way to understand 
        the state of public opinion or knowledge on many topics, including politics, 
        scientific understanding, brand recognition, and more. The ultimate goal in 
        taking a poll is generally to use the responses to estimate the opinion or 
        knowledge of the broader population.
      </p>
    </introduction>

