  <!-- Section 5.2: Confidence intervals -->
  <section xml:id="sec-confidence-intervals">
    <title>Confidence intervals for a proportion</title>

    <introduction>
      <p>
        A point estimate provides a single plausible value for a parameter. However, 
        a point estimate is rarely perfect; usually there is some error in the estimate. 
        Instead of supplying just a point estimate, a confidence interval provides a 
        plausible range of values for the parameter.
      </p>
    </introduction>

